Quote:  To name the biggest liar, or, the most constant talker. .in 4;`Old Dexter's talked us all down tonight. He hasn't stopped to draw breath. We unanimously agreed to give him the belt.' <i>Ibid.</i> 407 The ensign of a champion bestowed in name only. .in 4;`Harry can talk longer, and on more different topics than any of us, and after he had gone on non-stop most of the evening,we told him we'd give the belt for the greatest talker known among us all.'
